GPU Backend TODO
================
Target: OpenMP 5 target offload (gfortran -foffload=nvptx / nvfortran -mp=gpu)
Branch: refactor-hpc (continue here; tag rmsynth-hpc-gpu-v1 when validated)

FALLBACK GUARANTEE
------------------
If use_gpu=y but no GPU device is found at runtime, the code MUST silently
fall back to CPU without any user intervention. Implementation:
  - Call omp_get_num_devices() after cfg parse
  - Set use_gpu_actual = use_gpu .and. (omp_get_num_devices() > 0)
  - Print a WARNING message if falling back (not an error, not a stop)
  - All !$omp target directives carry if(use_gpu_actual)
  - When if() is false, OpenMP executes the block on the host transparently


STEP 1 — Tile scratch arrays: make per-pixel  [rm_synthesis.f]
---------------------------------------------------------------
Problem: Q_now(nz_out), U_now(nz_out), wts_now are single shared work arrays
         reused serially per pixel. GPU needs one copy per thread.

Replace:
  allocate(wts_now(ngood_chan))
  Q_now / U_now declared as fixed work arrays

With:
  allocate(Q_tile   (nx_tile * ny_tile * nz_out))
  allocate(U_tile   (nx_tile * ny_tile * nz_out))
  allocate(wts_tile (nx_tile * ny_tile * nz_out))
  allocate(ngood_tile(nx_tile * ny_tile))   ! integer, count of valid chans per pix

Pixel offset inside tile:
  ipix = (iy_loc-1)*nx_tile + ix_loc            ! 1-based
  base = (ipix-1)*nz_out + 1                    ! start of this pixel's spectrum

Commit message: "step1/gpu: tile scratch arrays made per-pixel"


STEP 2 — New tile_extract_gpu subroutine (CPU only)  [rm_synthesis_mod.f90]
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Extract the channel-selection + DFT work into a single subroutine with a
flat pixel loop (ipix = 1, nx_tile*ny_tile) so it can later be annotated.

Signature (free-form Fortran):
  subroutine tile_extract_gpu(                         &
      specQ, specU, specMask, specI, flag_arr,          &
      cos_arr, sin_arr,                                 &
      Q_tile, U_tile, wts_tile, ngood_tile,             &
      p_tile_arr, phi_tile_arr,                         &
      mask_tile_arr, nvalid_tile_arr,                   &
      nx_tile, ny_tile, nz_out, nrm_out,                &
      remove_qu_bias, use_input_mask,                   &
      nan_check_on, resiQ, slopeQ, resiU, slopeU,      &
      rem_mean, output_mode, ap_angle_mode)

Inner loop:   do ipix = 1, nx_tile*ny_tile
                 -- channel selection into Q_tile/U_tile slices
                 -- call weighted DFT inline (not via extract_general_w
                    because that call itself can't be on a device yet)
              end do

At this step: NO !$omp target yet; verify benchmark matches current output.

