STEP 4 — Add !$omp target annotations  [rm_synthesis_mod.f90]
--------------------------------------------------------------
Inside tile_extract_gpu, change the pixel loop header to:

  !$omp target teams distribute parallel do if(use_gpu_actual)     &
  !$omp& default(none)                                             &
  !$omp& map(to: specQ, specU, cos_arr, sin_arr, flag_arr)         &
  !$omp& map(from: p_tile_arr, phi_tile_arr,                       &
  !$omp&          mask_tile_arr, nvalid_tile_arr)                   &
  !$omp& private(ipix, ix_loc, iy_loc, ...)
  do ipix = 1, nx_tile*ny_tile
    ...
  end do
  !$omp end target teams distribute parallel do

Notes:
  - cos_arr/sin_arr are read-only across all pixels; map(to) once per tile
  - specQ/specU already tile-sized; transfer cost is proportional to tile, not image
  - p_tile_arr / phi_tile_arr are write-only device->host
  - No CFITSIO calls inside the device region (host-only I/O stays outside)

Commit message: "step4/gpu: add omp target offload to tile_extract_gpu"


COMPILATION STRATEGY — DUAL BACKEND OPTIMALITY
-----------------------------------------------
The GPU refactor flips the parallelism level:
  current CPU:  !$omp parallel do over RM bins (nout) inside each pixel call
  after refactor: parallelise over pixels (nx_tile*ny_tile) for both backends
Pixels >> RM bins in a typical tile, so the refactor also improves CPU.

Three build modes:

  GPU=0 OMP=1 (pure CPU, maximum CPU performance)
  ---------------------------------------------------
  FC = gfortran
  FFLAGS = -O3 -march=native -fopenmp
  DEFINES = (none; USE_GPU not defined)
  Result: preprocessor strips all !$omp target; plain !$omp parallel do over
          pixels; full AVX2/AVX-512 SIMD; zero offload overhead.
  use_gpu is ignored even if set y in cfg (omp_get_num_devices returns 0).

  GPU=1 (GPU offload build)
  ---------------------------------------------------
  FC = nvfortran           (preferred; excellent CPU codegen for fallback too)
  FFLAGS = -O3 -mp=gpu -gpu=cc80,managed
  DEFINES = -DUSE_GPU
  Fallback FC = gfortran -O3 -fopenmp -foffload=nvptx-none -DUSE_GPU
  Result: !$omp target teams distribute compiled for GPU; host path also
          compiled at -O3 by nvfortran.

  GPU=1 binary, no GPU found at runtime (the fallback case)
  -----------------------------------------------------------
  use_gpu_actual = .false. (set by omp_get_num_devices() == 0 check)
  !$omp target if(.false.) teams distribute parallel do
    -> OpenMP spec mandates host execution; threads spread over pixels
  Performance: near-native with nvfortran; within ~5% of GPU=0 build.
  For a CPU-only HPC node, best practice is to submit with GPU=0 binary.
  The GPU=1 fallback is a convenience safety net, not the performance target.

Source-level guard (in tile_extract_gpu and rm_synthesis_mod.f90):
  #ifdef USE_GPU
    !$omp target teams distribute parallel do if(use_gpu_actual) &
    !$omp& map(to: specQ,specU,cos_arr,sin_arr,flag_arr) &
    !$omp& map(from: p_tile_arr,phi_tile_arr,mask_tile_arr,nvalid_tile_arr)
  #else
    !$omp parallel do default(none) shared(...) private(ipix,...)
  #endif
    do ipix = 1, nx_tile*ny_tile
      ...
    end do
  #ifdef USE_GPU
    !$omp end target teams distribute parallel do
  #else
    !$omp end parallel do
  #endif

This ensures:
  - GPU=0 binary: maximum CPU performance, no offload overhead at all
  - GPU=1 binary + GPU present: full device offload
  - GPU=1 binary + no GPU: safe host fallback with warning, close to CPU perf
  - User experience: compile once for target, run anywhere without crashes


STEP 5 — cfg key + Makefile GPU target  [rm_synthesis_mod.f90, rm_synthesis.f, Makefile]
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Config key (default n, backward compatible):
  use_gpu = y|n

Parser: add case 'use_gpu' alongside dry_run / tile_auto (flag_from_value).

Runtime check (add after cfg parse in rm_synthesis.f):
  use_gpu_actual = .false.
  if (use_gpu) then
    use_gpu_actual = (omp_get_num_devices() > 0)
    if (.not. use_gpu_actual) then
      write(*,*) 'WARNING: use_gpu=y requested but no GPU device found.'
      write(*,*) 'WARNING: Falling back to CPU execution transparently.'
    else
      write(*,*) 'GPU device found. Offloading tile kernel to GPU.'
    endif
  endif

Makefile GPU=1 mode (nvfortran preferred; gfortran fallback):
  ifeq ($(GPU),1)
    FC = nvfortran
    FFLAGS_EXTRA = -mp=gpu -gpu=cc80,managed
    # fallback: FC = gfortran; FFLAGS_EXTRA = -foffload=nvptx-none -fopenmp
  endif

Commit message: "step5/gpu: add use_gpu cfg key, runtime fallback, GPU=1 makefile target"


