NOTES / RISKS
-------------
- wts_now allocation currently sized to ngood_chan (post-bad-channel removal).
  After step 1, wts_tile is sized to nz_out (max possible); zero-fill unused slots.
- mean_rem (Q/U mean removal) uses a reduction over nz_out; fine on GPU as
  !$omp simd reduction already present in extract_general_w; replicate inline
  in tile_extract_gpu.
- ap_angle_mode half-angle scaling (phi_ex *= 0.5) is per-RM-bin, trivially
  device-safe.
- CFITSIO writes stay host-side; device->host transfer of p_tile_arr happens
  at the end of each tile, same cadence as current CPU writes.
- If nvfortran is unavailable, gfortran -foffload=nvptx-none works for NVIDIA;
  for AMD use -foffload=amdgcn-amdhsa. Both honour the same !$omp target syntax.
